author: julianfoad
msg: Change the symmetric merge base-finding subroutines to always report a base,
even if it's the YCA, and to choose base-on-source in preference to
base-on-target if they're the same location.  (The latter obviously doesn't
matter in theory, but at present the subsequent code path explicitly depends
on which was chosen, and the resulting notifications differ.)
find_symmetric_merge): Report the YCA rather than NULL.
